results.name: Number of divisors of n which are not also differences between consecutive divisors (ordered by increasing magnitude) of n.
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..65537
example: For n=70, divisors={1,2,5,7,10,14,35,70}; differences={1,3,2,3,4,21,35}; the divisors {5,7,10,14,70} are not differences, so a(70)=5.
program: (PARI) A060764(n) = { my(divs=divisors(n), diffs=vecsort(vector(#divs-1,i,divs[i+1]-divs[i]), ,8), c=#divs); for(i=1,#diffs,if(!(n%diffs[i]),c--)); (c); }; \\ _Antti Karttunen_, Sep 21 2018
